FT  18 MAR 92 / UK Company News: Amey drives up 27% to Pounds 2.8m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Amey Holdings, the private contractor, reported a 27 per cent rise in
pre-tax profits from Pounds 2.2m to Pounds 2.8m for 1991. Turnover rose 53
per cent to Pounds 145m.
The company said as a result of a marketing drive turnover in its roads side
improved from Pounds 37m to Pounds 62m while building sales quadrupled to
Pounds 31m.
Earnings per share were 352p (311p).
