<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAR 92 / The Lex Column: US economy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The latest evidence of US economic recovery is not as decisive as Mr Bush
would like at this stage of the election process. Housing starts began to
pick up in the fourth quarter of last year, so the further improvement in
February, although welcome, is of limited value until there are additional
signs that consumer confidence is recovering. Hence yesterday's reversal of
an over-hasty jump in Treasury bond yields. All the same, the trend is
worrying for Wall Street. At their present high levels, the last thing US
equities need is a bond market in which yields rise every time recovery
moves a little closer.
</TEXT>
