<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAR 92 / Election '92: Aslef halts campaign on sell-off
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ASLEF, the train drivers' union, yesterday postponed a campaign against rail
privatisation after legal advisers said that it should not go ahead during
the election campaign, Michael Smith writes.
The union was told that it could be open to a challenge that it was
providing hidden finance for the Labour party, which opposes privatisation.
The Trades Union Congress is also advising unions that local Labour party
agents must be consulted on anything that promotes the party and its
candidates. Aslef did not have time to contact them before today's scheduled
launch.
</TEXT>
