<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAR 92 / Friendly societies widen their scope
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FRIENDLY societies, the institutions born out of the co-operative movement
to sell products such as insurance and investment schemes, have won the
right to extend the scope of their financial services.
Under the Friendly Societies Bill, which has passed through parliament, they
can opt for corporate status and form incorporated subsidiaries offering new
services.
The Act will establish a new regulatory framework, including a Friendly
Societies Commission. Friendly societies will also be brought within the
scope of the Policyholders Protection Act 1975.
The Registry of Friendly societies will have to change its regulations
before friendly societies can take advantage of the new legislation. That
process could take another year.
</TEXT>
