<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAR 92 / Stewards at Rover back work changes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SHOP STEWARDS represent-ing more than 30,000 Rover car workers yesterday
agreed to recommend acceptance of radical Japanese-style working practices.
The workforce will have the final say in a ballot next month but is expected
to approve the package, heralded as one of the biggest shake-ups for years
in car-plant industrial relations.
It will guarantee some workers jobs for life, scrap nearly all shop-floor
demarcation and open the way for flexible team working. It also promises
that there will be no more compulsory redundancies. The age-old ritual of
clocking-on would be scrapped.
