The Iranian deputy foreign minister, Mr Mahmoud Vaezi, left for Baku
yesterday to follow up Tehran's mediation in the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict,
the Iranian news agency, Irna, reported, Reuter reports from Nicosia. Mr
Vaezi will try to build on a draft truce signed in Tehran last Sunday.
