<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CBR, the Belgian cement group, yesterday reported a 12.4 per cent drop in
1991 profits to BFr3.63bn (Dollars 105m), but in the light of expansion in
North America and Europe announced a BFr20 per share increase in dividend to
BFr270.
Profits followed the downturn in Europe and recession in North America, the
company explained. However, the volume of its business held up, and because
it bought several US companies making ready-mixed concrete and building
aggregates, overall group turnover rose last year by 7.2 per cent to
BFr46.33bn.
