Belgian parent company, to BFr1.95bn last year compared with BFr4.26bn in
1990, when the company recorded some extraordinary profits from leading
subsidiaries.
Cash-flow expanded as the group increased investment in the Tehchapi cement
plant in California and expanded its Tilbury plant in British Columbia. It
further strengthened its west coast presence by buying ready-mixed concrete
and aggregate companies in California, Washington state and Alberta, as well
as closer to home in Belgium, Germany and the Netherlands.
Early this year, it took a stake in Mokra, a leading southern Czech cement
producer, of which it will gain majority control by the end of 1994.
