FT  18 MAR 92 / Letter: A point about the HIV virus
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr STEPHEN T MELDRUM
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Dominic Lawson underestimates the incidence of the HIV virus ('Sex and
the single company', March 14). 0.04 per cent is 1 in 2,500 (not 1 in 4,000)
and 0.016 per cent is 1 in 6,250 (not 1 in 16,000). By Mr Lawson's maths the
more precision in the percentage the less the likelihood. A few more decimal
places would make the HlV virus a mere curiosity.
Stephen T Meldrum,
White's Hill,
Amersham Road,
Beaconsfield, Bucks HP9 2UG
</TEXT>
