<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 92 / International Company News: Nike posts strong advance in
third period
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SEATTLE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
NIKE, the US sport shoes group, yesterday reported strong international
sales growth and an advance in profits for the third quarter, Reuter reports
from Seattle.
The company said worldwide orders for its athletic footwear and apparel
scheduled for delivery between March and July 1992 was about Dollars 1.4bn,
up 15 per cent over the same period a year earlier.
In the third quarter, the group lifted net earnings to Dollars 82.5m from
Dollars 70.7m the previous year which took earnings per share for the period
to Dollars 1.08, against 93 cents. Revenues advanced to Dollars 867m from
Dollars 802.2m.
Nike said it expected to achieve higher earnings in its fourth fiscal
quarter ending May 31. In the same period of 1991, the group earned 76 cents
a share, down from 89 cents.
Mr Philip Knight, chairman, said the company's strong international growth
was highlighted in Germany, where it posted a 59 per cent rise in sales.
He added that the boost in sales in Germany had moved it to the number two
sales spot in that country for the first time, ahead of Puma, and gaining
ground on its rival, Adidas.
'In the US, where we have maintained our 31 per cent market share, future
orders indicate renewed domestic growth will occur in the next quarter,' he
added.
