<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 92 / International Capital Markets: CLBN secures further loan
guarantees
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROTTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CREDIT Lyonnais, the French state-owned bank, has provided an extra Fl 3bn
in loan guarantees to Credit Lyonnais Nederland Bank (CLBN), its 94 per cent
owned Dutch subsidiary, Reuter reports from Rotterdam.
Credit Lyonnais now stands as guarantor for nearly Fl 5bn of CLBN's debts,
up from Fl 2bn in mid-1991.
CLBN yesterday announced that net profits in 1991 more than halved to Fl
30.1m from Fl 63.4m the previous year.
Credit Lyonnais last year provided Fl 2bn in guarantees for CLBN loans to Mr
Giancarlo Parretti, the Italian financier.
The Dutch bank had loans of USDollars 888m outstanding to Mr Parretti as of
July 1991. The bulk financed his 1990 takeover of MGM, the US film studio
which sank into financial crisis last year.
Westdeutsche Landesbank Girozentrale (WestLB) said it and the
Sudwest-Deutsche Landesbank Girozentrale (SudwestLB) have combined their
activities in Switzerland.
