<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 92 / UK Company News: Publishing performance gives BPP lift to
Pounds 6.4m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROLAND RUDD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BPP HOLDINGS, the financial training and publishing group, announced pre-tax
profits 23 per cent ahead, up from Pounds 5.19m to Pounds 6.39m, for the
1991 year.
A strong performance from publishing offset a fall in profits from training
and language courses. These were hit by lower recruitment of chartered
accountants and the Gulf war.
Mr Richard Price, chairman, said: 'We like to think we are a good each way
bet for the general election. If the Conservatives win it will be good for
the underlying strength of the economy, while if Labour wins it will be good
for training.'
Earnings per share increased to 17.3p (15.7p) as sales rose to Pounds 42.4m
(Pounds 36.7m). An increased final dividend of 4.5p lifts the total to 6.9p
(6.3p).
There was an extraordinary charge of Pounds 362,000 to cover the costs of
closing BPP Management Education and the unsuccessful legal action to lift
an injunction preventing the group from bidding for DC Gardner.
In May the group raised Pounds 12.3m by way of a rights issue, used to
acquire Letts Educational, a publisher of home-study books for school
examinations, for Pounds 3.7m, and the purchase of 75 per cent of Melrose, a
publisher of video-based training packages, for Pounds 5.75m. The group now
has net cash of Pounds 5.2m and is looking at various publishing companies
to buy.
The publishing activities all did well, benefiting from the rise in numbers
of college students, and increased profits to Pounds 1.95m (Pounds 1.27m).
</TEXT>
